article.headline: CS Bakersfield 98, Loyola Marymount 64
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. (AP) -- Demarcus Hall had a career-high 23 points and 13 rebounds to help Cal State Bakersfield to a 98-64 victory over Loyola Marymount on Monday night. Terrence Johns scored 21 points, 17 coming in the first half for Bakersfield (4-2), which raced to a 29-11 lead in the opening 5:34. The Roadrunners led by as many 30 points in the final minute before halftime en route to a season-high for points in their first year at the NCAA Division I level. Hall also had 13 rebounds and Donavan Bragg contributed eight assists for Bakersfield. Loyola Marymount (3-13) never got closer than 25 points in the second half. Orlando Johnson scored 14 points and Brandon Walker had 11 for Loyola, which lost its fifth in a row.
